nd Reusability) principles. By adhering to these principles, researchers can significantly enhance the transparency, efficiency, and impact of their work beyond the project. Ultimately, a FAIR compliant data resource not only promotes collaboration and innovation but also ensures compliance with institutional and funding agency requirements, ultimately advancing the scientific community's collective knowledge.\n\nThis SOP describes a potential approach to evaluate the FAIRness level of the datasets and proposes opportunities for data dissemination into public repositories.", "metadata": {"doc_id": "bff29c7e-c9ef-4a71-9b86-0aca230428d4", "content_type": "CompositeElement", "filename": "R4ALL_SOP_FairDataAssessment.pdf"}}